  subhead="A homeowner calls at 11am on a Monday. His BMW iX has arrived three days early — it is sitting on the driveway in Witney with 180 miles of range and no home charger. The house is a 2010 four-bedroom detached with a double garage. The consumer unit is in the utility room at the back of the house — approximately twelve metres from the mounting position on the front garage wall. He wants an Ohme Home Pro 7kW tethered in black, with the OZEV EVHS grant applied. The house has a PME supply but he has read that some installations need a TT conversion with an earth rod. He is on Octopus Intelligent Go and wants the charger to schedule overnight charging automatically at the 7.5p rate. His wife is getting a Hyundai Ioniq 5 next month, so he wants to know whether one 7kW charger can serve both vehicles. You are at a workplace car park in Abingdon — installing eight Pod Point Twin 2x7kW chargers on steel posts with concrete foundations, running SWA from the three-phase distribution board in the building to each post position. The 10mm² armoured cable trenches across the car park, the cable glands seal, and the RCBO boards wire. Without AI Phone Answering, the Witney dual-vehicle household goes to voicemail. The iX sits with 180 miles. With it, the AI captures: Witney 2010 4-bed detached double garage, Ohme Home Pro 7kW black tethered, 12m cable run utility to front garage, PME supply TT question, OZEV EVHS, Octopus Intelligent Go 7.5p overnight, BMW iX + Hyundai Ioniq 5 next month, dual-vehicle question."
  scenario="It is 2pm on a Thursday. Three calls between noon and 2pm. You are inside a consumer unit at a property in Eynsham — isolating the supply, fitting a Hager RCBO board with a dedicated 32A Type A RCBO for the EV circuit, terminating the 10mm² SWA twin and earth from the Zappi v2 on the outside wall, and testing the earth loop impedance on the new TT system after driving the earth rod to 12 ohms. Without AI Phone Answering, one voicemail and two hang-ups. With it, all three answered. Lead one: a property developer in Carterton — 'building sixty houses, need per-plot EV charger pre-wire with draw cord and back box, NHBC compliant, want pricing per plot.' Lead two: a Tesla Model Y owner in Didcot — 'just collected my car, want a Tesla Wall Connector Gen 3, my garage has power but I think the consumer unit is full.' Lead three: a pub landlord in Woodstock — 'want two destination chargers in the car park for customers, need contactless payment, will the 100A single-phase supply handle them or do I need a three-phase upgrade?' At 2:30pm the Ze reads 0.8 ohms. Three leads — a sixty-house developer, a Tesla garage install, and a pub destination project."
